contentfulPagePressRelease.title: Algerian PM Visits QF Ahead of Arab League Summit

childMarkdownRemark.html:
Qatar Foundation for Education, Science and Community Development hosted His Excellency Mr Abdelmalek Sellal, Prime Minister of the Democratic People’s Republic of Algeria on Monday, 25 March. A welcoming committee led by Mr Rashed Al-Qurese, Qatar Foundation’s Deputy Director of Communication, received the Prime Minister and his delegation at the Qatar Foundation Visitors Center.

Alongside Mr Sellal, members of the Algerian party included His Excellency Mr Mourad Medelci, Algerian Minister of Foreign Affairs, His Excellency Mr Mustapha Benbada, Algerian Minister of Commerce and His Excellency Abdul Fattah Ziani, Algerian Ambassador to Qatar. His Excellency Abdullah bin Nasser Al-Humaidi, Qatari Ambassador to Algeria, also accompanied the delegation.

The delegation was briefed on Qatar Foundation’s numerous sustainability initiatives and climate action solutions. After the presentation, Prime Minister Sellal and his delegation were shown an impressive 3D scale model of the current buildings and future construction projects at Qatar Foundation.
